* CRITICAL: Commit Message Format Rules (MANDATORY - STRICTLY ENFORCED)
  * When generating ANY commit message, you MUST follow this EXACT format:
  * 
  * REQUIRED FORMAT (NO EXCEPTIONS):
  * 1. First line: Brief summary in imperative mood (MAX 50 characters)
  * 2. Second line: Empty line
  * 3. Third line onwards: Bullet points starting with "- " (hyphen space)
  * 4. Each bullet point should be a single action/item
  * 5. NEVER write in paragraph or prose format
  * 6. NEVER use sentences like "This commit...", "We updated...", "The changes include..."
  * 7. ALWAYS use imperative mood: "Add", "Fix", "Update", "Remove", "Refactor"
  * 8. ALWAYS write in English only
  * 
  * FORBIDDEN FORMATS (NEVER USE):
  * - DO NOT write: "Refactor deployment scripts and backend models to improve clarity..."
  * - DO NOT write: "This commit adds..." or "We updated..." or "The changes include..."
  * - DO NOT write multi-sentence paragraphs
  * - DO NOT exceed 50 characters on first line
  * - DO NOT use past tense: "Added", "Fixed", "Updated" (use "Add", "Fix", "Update")
  
* REQUIRED Format Template:
  * [Summary line - max 50 chars]
  * 
  * - [First change]
  * - [Second change]
  * - [Third change]
  
* CORRECT Examples (USE THIS FORMAT):
  * Example 1:
  * Refactor deployment scripts and translate to English
  * 
  * - Translate all Python scripts to English
  * - Update backend models structure
  * - Improve error messages
  * 
  * Example 2:
  * Add release and deployment management
  * 
  * - Add Release model and API endpoints
  * - Add Deployment model with batch support
  * - Update backend main.py with new routes
  * 
  * Example 3:
  * Update commit message rules to bullet format
  * 
  * - Update commit-message.mdc rules
  * - Update .gitmessage template
  * - Add explicit format requirements
  * 
  * Example 4:
  * Apply rules and translate code to English
  * 
  * - Translate Python deployment scripts
  * - Translate C# Agent code
  * - Update commit message format rules
  * - Add Release and Deployment models
